# Compose

## Recomposition Optimization

### @Immutable for UI models

All UI data classes in `presentation/models/` are annotated with `@Immutable`:

```kotlin
@Immutable
data class Ui{Feature}State(
    val value: String = "",
    val isLoading: Boolean = false,
)
```

`@Immutable` is only placed in modules with Compose dependencies (presentation, ui). Module `common` is pure Kotlin — no Compose Runtime.

### rememberUpdatedState for callbacks in effects

Required for callbacks inside `LaunchedEffect` / `DisposableEffect` to always have the latest instance without restarting the effect:

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun SomeEffect(onAction: () -> Unit) {
    val currentOnAction by rememberUpdatedState(onAction)

    LaunchedEffect(Unit) {
        // use currentOnAction() — always fresh, no effect restart
    }
}
```

### remember for modifier depending on parameters

```kotlin
val modifier = remember(paddingValues) { Modifier.padding(paddingValues) }
```

### derivedStateOf for derived state

Use when state is computed from another state and recomposition on every source change is not needed:

```kotlin
val showButton by remember {
    derivedStateOf { lazyListState.firstVisibleItemIndex > 0 }
}
```

### key for LazyColumn items

Always provide `key` for `LazyColumn` items:

```kotlin
LazyColumn {
    items(items = items, key = { it.id }) { item ->
        ItemCard(item = item)
    }
}
```

## Composable Components (splitting rules)

### Pass minimum required data

Pass only what child composables need — not the entire state object:

```kotlin
// ✅ Correct
{Feature}Content(
    value = state.value,
    isLoading = state.isLoading,
    onNextClick = onNextClick,
)

// ❌ Wrong
{Feature}Content(state = state)
```

### LaunchedEffect / SideEffect placement

Place at the **beginning** of the composable function, before UI content. Extract complex effects into separate composables.

## Preview for UI Components

Every composable component in UI modules must have a `@Preview` function in the same file.

Rules:
- Name: `Preview` + component name (e.g. `PreviewItemCard`)
- Always `@Preview(showBackground = true)`
- Wrapped in `KmmTemplateTheme { }`
- For components with multiple states — show variants in a `Column`

```kotlin
@Preview(showBackground = true)
@Composable
private fun PreviewItemCard() {
    KmmTemplateTheme {
        Column(
            modifier = Modifier.padding(16.dp),
            verticalArrangement = Arrangement.spacedBy(12.dp),
        ) {
            ItemCard(/* example data */)
        }
    }
}
```
